<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by euthanatos on 05-06-2002 03:57 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Holy ****, you guys are killing me, so many posts and I gotta go through them to extract all valuable feedback (and believe me there is) ;p I'll try to answer questions where I can but don't shoot me if I overlook some

 [QUOTE]Originally posted by Anthea:
[i]
- The texts shown over the potions are not always correct.[/i][/QUOTE]
How do you mean not correct? If it is the number behind the potion name not being right or even the whole description not fitting (like saying a health potion is a mana potion) than we are aware of the problem and it's partly solved atm, if not please specify what the exact problem was  :)
 [QUOTE]Originally posted by Anthea:
[i]
- If I have a special type of potion no more, it is still shown in the "browse potions" icons.[/i][/QUOTE]
As pointed out earlier this is as intended. The icon does change though: it greys out. This was done so once you pick up potions they stay in a fixed order(so after a while you can click almost blindly cause they're always in the same order
 [QUOTE]Originally posted by Anthea:
[i]
- The focus of the mouse is sometimes not right. If there are several containers, some destroyed in the background, and a normal one in the foreground, right in front of each other, it was very difficult to touch the one in the foreground, for always the crushed one was selected. .[/i][/QUOTE]
This is indeed a problem but we're aware of it and is on the TODO list ;p
 [QUOTE]Originally posted by Sabbath Hornblower:
[i]The list in "Personal Traits" didn't update for all entries, my constitution was still 10 there, even when I had finished the game (and Con was really 22). The one below didn't update either (hp, mp).
[/i][/QUOTE] This problem is already fixed  :)
 [QUOTE]Originally posted by Moriendor:
[i]1) Why does Grugar, the zombie, attack the orcs around Smiruk? Seems like a logical bug. If I am neutral towards them then Grugar should not attack them either.[/i][/QUOTE] If you think about this it is somehow logical: zombie sees orcs, thinks orcs are bad and attacks them, other way round orcs are used to killing zombies so no reason why they shouldn't attack him
 [QUOTE]Originally posted by Moriendor:
[i]5) Why does the mini map keep on disappearing when you change levels? It's sort of annyoing when you always have to hit the "M" key after changing locations..[/i][/QUOTE] It stays right now, so bug solved  :)
 [QUOTE]Originally posted by Gatalas:
[i]2. One time I loaded the game and all enemies were friendly to me and I wasn't able to attack any more. Running through the orc camp without being bothered... Yeah!   ;)
4. At the moment I have for some reason unlimited stamina it just won't get less.[/i][/QUOTE]Are known and fixed
 [QUOTE]Originally posted by CarPd13m:
[i][b]1-[/b] killed jake twice..[/i][/QUOTE] Completely normal, you'll encounter him again later on in the game, he's sort of an easter egg
 [QUOTE]Originally posted by CarPd13m:
[i][b]5-[/b] pause - meteorite - pause - meteorite -pause - meteorite -pause - meteorite -pause - meteorite is far to effective
[b]6-[/b] used [i]5-[/i] to finnish the game very quickly[/I][/QUOTE] Was indeed very powerfull but we're balancing skills at the moment so expect some changes there


